Fifteen years of loving you 🤎
“Let me not to the marriage of true minds
Admit impediments. Love is not love
Which alters when it alteration finds,
Or bends with the remover to remove:
O no! it is an ever-fixed mark
That looks on tempests and is never shaken;
It is the star to every wandering bark,
Whose worth's unknown, although his height be taken.
Love's not Time's fool, though rosy lips and cheeks
Within his bending sickle's compass come:
Love alters not with his brief hours and weeks,
But bears it out even to the edge of doom.
If this be error and upon me proved,
I never writ, nor no man ever loved.”
Sonnet 116, William Shakespeare 
•
I surely would not be who I am if not for your love. My greatest support, nurturer of every dream. You are the best part of me, “…and I love, I love, I love you” 🕊️

2023 • What a truly beautiful year! 
A year of healing, creating and pursuit of beauty — whilst living in SO much love. 
•
Our year began in the best way possible, getting the keys to our home! Then all the beautiful daffodils, hellebores and spring blooms soon followed, our dream garden slowly taking shape… Months of bountiful harvest, barefoot days and chasing butterflies. Jane turns 4. Our suitcases packed for a most wonderful summer holiday to England and France! Chateau, wine, baguette, repeat. Returning home gave way to endless tomato sandwiches and days by the pool. Summer quickly turning to autumn, another year older, a turn of a decade, 30 🤎 Golden hues, so much magic in the foliage! Autumn came and went and at last, Christmas. There was growth, so much healing and I am so grateful for God’s leadership over our lives. Our pursuit to follow His will continues on 🤍 Farewell to this year!
Fresh beginnings • Aligning my heart to tenderness… In motherhood, in designs, in creations - and all aspects of life 🤍
